<TITLE> Former IOs sued in Aug 21 grenade case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 30 (bdnews24.com)  Police have filed a case against three former CID investigation officers of the August 21 2004 grenade attack case, accusing them of presenting false witnesses in court and concealing information, said police on Monday. The accused are former assistant superintendents of police Abdur Rashid and Munshi Atiqul Islam and special superintendent of police Ruhul Amin. ASP Fazlul Kabir, the incumbent investigation officer in the case, filed the case with Paltan Police Station in the city on Sunday night. Sub-inspector of Paltan police Mahmud Hossain told bdnews24.com that the case accuses the three officers of forcing Jodge Mia to give false statement in court. It also accuses them of concealing evidence regarding the brutal attack on an Awami League rally in 2004 that left at least 24 dead and injured the then opposition leader Sheikh Hasina. bd
